{"title_page": "Ceva Sant\u00e9 Animale", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n| name = Ceva Sant\u00e9 Animale\n| logo = \n| type = \n| industry = [[Veterinary medicine]]\n| fate = \n| predecessors = [[Sanofi]]<br> Synth\u00e9labo\n| successor = <!-- or: | successors = -->\n| founded = {{Start date and age|1999}}\n| founder = <!-- or: | founders = -->\n| defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| hq_location_city = [[Libourne]]\n| hq_location_country = France\n| area_served = <!-- or: | areas_served = -->\n| key_people = Marc Prikazsky ([[CEO]] & [[Chairman]])\n| products = \n| owner = <!-- or: | owners = -->\n| num_employees = 5,700\n| num_employees_year = \n| parent = \n| website = {{URL|ceva.com/en}}\n}}\n'''Ceva Sant\u00e9 Animale''' (Ceva) is a multinational animal health company based in [[Libourne]], France. Established in 1999, Ceva undertakes research, development, production and marketing of pharmaceutical products and vaccines, and also provides complementary services and equipment, for companion animals, poultry, ruminants and swine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thepoultrysite.com/poultrynews/39902/ceva-launches-a-new-wave-of-innovation-to-help-poultry-producers-meet-the-performance-challenges-driven-by-the-need-for-no-antibiotics-and-more-sustainable-production/|title=Ceva launches a \"new wave of innovation\" to help poultry producers meet the performance challenges driven by the need for \"No antibiotics\" and more sustainable production|website=The Poultry Site|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref>\n\nCeva also supplies; hatchery vaccines, vaccination services and equipment; pheromone-based behavioural products for cats and dogs with additional knowledge in companion animal cardiology, locomotion and dermatology; products for the management of reproduction in ruminants such as antibiotic therapies and vaccines; and a growing range of products for swine, including antibiotic therapies, reproduction management and vaccines.\n\nWith revenues of US$1.16 billion (\u20ac1.1 billion) for 2017, Ceva is the 6th largest animal health company in the world and the biggest French multinational in the sector based on revenue.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.statista.com/statistics/260190/leading-animal-health-providers-based-on-revenue/|title=Top animal health companies by revenue worldwide 2017 {{!}} Statistic|website=Statista|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref>\n\nCeva is based in 45 countries and works in more than 110 countries worldwide. It has 12 research and development centres, 25 production sites and more than 5,500 employees.\n\nIn 2010, to mark its 10<sup>th</sup> anniversary, the company adopted a new mission statement, \u2018Together, we are building a new reference to create value beyond animal health\u2019, abbreviated in the slogan to \u2018Together, beyond animal health\u2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://animalpharm.agribusinessintelligence.informa.com/AP005120/Ceva---Together-beyond-animal-health|title=Ceva - 'Together beyond animal health'|date=2010-11-26|website=Animal Pharm|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nThe Chairman and CEO is Marc Prikazsky.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/tosv2.html?vid=&uuid=d4260350-2e16-11e9-8043-9b0a5f1e26ed&url=L3Jlc2VhcmNoL3N0b2Nrcy9wcml2YXRlL3BlcnNvbi5hc3A/cGVyc29uSWQ9NDI3NDI2ODQmcHJpdmNhcElkPTEzNTU3OSZwcmV2aW91c0NhcElkPTE5MTE1JnByZXZpb3VzVGl0bGU9QkMlMjUyNTI1MjBQYXJ0bmVycw==|title=Bloomberg - Are you a robot?|website=www.bloomberg.com|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nCeva is accused of participating in serious treatment of [[Mare|mares]] to provide [[equine chorionic gonadotropin]].\n\n== History ==\nIn 1999, two French pharmaceutical companies, [[Sanofi]] and Synth\u00e9labo, merged to form Sanofi-Synth\u00e9labo. Soon after the merger, the new company divested several businesses, including its animal health and nutrition business, Sanofi Sant\u00e9 Nutrition Animale.\n\nThis business was acquired through the first of four [[Leveraged buyout|leveraged management buyouts]] (LMBO) and resulted in the establishment in 1999 of Ceva Sant\u00e9 Animal. Following the third LMBO, in 2007 Ceva management and employees acquired the majority shareholding in the company.\n\nIn 2014, there was a Reshaping of Ceva's capital structure to accompany the launch of the company's ambition to become the first independent player within the top 5 global animal health companies by 2020. While management still retained the position of majority shareholders long-term strategic partners were selected to support the group's future growth ambitions:[[Temasek Holdings|Temasek]], [[CDH Investments]], Euromezzanine, [[About:blank|Sagard]] and M\u00e9rieux D\u00e9veloppement.\n\nSince 1999, Ceva has been the sole shareholder of Ceva-Phylaxia. Founded in Hungary in 1912, the Phylaxia Vaccine Production Co produced the first vaccine against [[classical swine fever]]. Scientists including [[J\u00f3zsef Marek]] and [[Alad\u00e1r Aujeszky]] were closely associated with the company. \n\nCeva has grown rapidly through both acquisitions and organic growth. In 2000 it ranked 18<sup>th</sup> globally with sales of US$140 million a year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://animalpharm.agribusinessintelligence.informa.com/AP012786/A-carousel-of-companies-Inside-the-industry-consolidation-of-19902000|title=A carousel of companies: Inside the industry consolidation of 1990-2000|date=2017-08-03|website=Animal Pharm|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\n'''Major acquisitions by Ceva include:''' \n\n* 2017: Purchase of ex-Merial product range<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://animalpharm.agribusinessintelligence.informa.com/AP011375/Ceva-closes-acquisition-of-Merial-assets|title=Ceva closes acquisition of Merial assets|date=2017-01-19|website=Animal Pharm|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n* 2017: Joint-venture agreement between EBVAC, China and Ceva to create a new business, Ceva Ebvac, focused on the swine vaccine sector\n* 2016: Hertape Saude Animale Ltda. and Inova Biotecnologia Saude Animale Ltda, Brazil, \n* 2016: Biovac, a manufacturer of autogeneous (bacterial) vaccines, allergy treatments and reagents based in Angers, France<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://objectifaquitaine.latribune.fr/business/2016-06-02/ceva-sante-animale-acquiert-le-laboratoire-biovac.html|title=Ceva Sant\u00e9 animale acquiert le laboratoire Biovac|website=La Tribune|language=fr|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n* 2015: Polchem, India<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20160308006326/en/Ceva-Reports-Annual-Growth-12-Reaffirms-Ambition|title=Ceva Reports Annual Growth of 12% and Reaffirms Ambition to Enter the Global Top 5 by 2020|date=2016-03-08|website=www.businesswire.com|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n* 2013: Sogeval \n* 2011: Vetech Laboratories, Inc., a Canadian poultry vaccine manufacturer that produces live coccidiosis vaccines for poultry under the trade name Immucox\u00ae \n* 2011: First joint venture established in China, Ceva Huadu\n* 2010: Summit VetPharm, a New Jersey-based company\n* 2005: Biomune, a US poultry vaccine producer based in [[Lenexa, Kansas|Lenexa]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kclifesciences.org/news/life-sciences-bulletin/volume-1-2014/ceva-going-beyond-animal-health/|title=Ceva: Going Beyond Animal Health {{!}} Kansas City Area Life Sciences Institute|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and recognition ==\nIn 2016, Ceva won the best company in Europe category in Animal Pharm's annual industry awards.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pig333.com/company_news/ceva-best-company-in-europe-winner-animal-pharm-awards-2016_12105/|title=Ceva: Best Company in Europe winner Animal Pharm awards 2016|website=www.pig333.com|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Ceva's hatchery vaccination services program for poultry, the C.H.I.C.K Program, received quality recognition from the international testing and certification company, Bureau Veritas Group, based in Paris. This was the first time a services program delivered by an animal health company had received internationally recognised quality approval.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thepoultrysite.com/focus/ceva/2790/ceva-hatchery-services-chick-program|title=Ceva - Hatchery Services - C.H.I.C.K. Program|website=The Poultry Site|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nSince 2005, Ceva has been awarded six International Cat Care (ICC) Easy to Give Awards. It has also received three ICC Cat Friendly Awards for products in the [[Cat pheromone|Feliway]] range. The Cat Friendly Awards recognise products which have made a real difference to cat wellbeing and welfare.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://icatcare.org/about-us/awards|title=Our awards {{!}} International Cat Care|website=icatcare.org|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\n== Key partnerships ==\nCeva established a partnership with the l\u2019Association Chiens Guides d'Aveugles Ali\u00e9nor (guide dogs for the blind association).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chiensguides-alienor.com/|title=Ecole de chiens guides Ali\u00e9nor-Sud-Ouest|website=www.chiensguides-alienor.com|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\n'''2018'''\n\nCeva is associated with the [[Union Bordeaux B\u00e8gles]], a French rugby union team. The team's new performance centre, inaugurated in October at the Moga stadium in B\u00e8gles, has been named the Ceva Campus.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sudouest.fr/2018/10/04/-5446383-4583.php|title=L'UBB dispose d'un bel outil|website=SudOuest.fr|language=fr-FR|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nWageningen Bioveterinary Research (WBVR) and Ceva are developing veterinary vaccines for the control of (re)emerging infectious animal diseases, such as Rift Valley fever and Influenza.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thepoultrysite.com/poultrynews/40117/wageningen-bioveterinary-research-and-ceva-form-strategic-alliance-to-counter-global-threat-of-emerging-and-reemerging-diseases/|title=Wageningen Bioveterinary Research and Ceva form strategic alliance to counter global threat of emerging and re-emerging diseases|website=The Poultry Site|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nThe North Carolina State College of Veterinary Medicine and Ceva are collaborating on a distance learning project providing certification in poultry health management for veterinarians in Latin America.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thepoultrysite.com/poultrynews/39785/cvm-and-ceva-enter-educational-partnership-for-latin-american-veterinarians/|title=CVM and Ceva enter educational partnership for Latin American veterinarians|website=The Poultry Site|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\n'''2017'''\n\n[[World Veterinary Association|The World Veterinary Association]] (WVA) created the Global Animal Welfare Awards, co-founded and supported by Ceva, to recognize and reward veterinarians who contribute to the protection and welfare of animals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldvet.org/news.php?item=322|title=WVA News|website=www.worldvet.org|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nThe World Veterinary Poultry Association (WVPA) and Ceva launched a digital library resource on poultry veterinary medicine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wvpa.net/library.php|title=WVPA|website=www.wvpa.net|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\n'''2015'''\n\nCeva is involved in a program to supply Australia's wildlife veterinarians with an antibiotic to treat [[Chlamydia infection|chlamydia]] disease in koala's free of charge.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fiercepharma.com/r-d/ceva-combats-chlamydia-australian-koalas-new-program|title=Ceva combats chlamydia in Australian koalas with new program {{!}} FiercePharma|website=www.fiercepharma.com|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nCeva partnered with WikiVet to develop a comprehensive on-line peer reviewed veterinary knowledge database and add a module on feline behaviour.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.wikivet.net/Feline_Behaviour|title=Feline Behaviour - WikiVet English|website=en.wikivet.net|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nCeva received a grant from the [[Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation]] to improve the lives of smallholder and poor village farmers by improving the health and productive capacity of poultry and cattle, species with significant economic importance to poor livestock keepers in developing countries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gatesfoundation.org/How-We-Work/Quick-Links/Grants-Database/Grants/2015/11/OPP1134139|title=OPP1134139|website=Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nCeva sponsored the UK Animal Welfare Awards, in partnership with the Veterinary Times and the VN Times.\n\n'''2012'''\n\nSince 2012, the Fondation du Patrimoine and Ceva, under the patronage of the French Ministry of Agriculture, have awarded the Fondation du Patrimoine National Animal Agro-Biodiversity Prize in recognition of initiatives to preserve and promote French rare breeds.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.togetherbeyondanimalhealth.com/ceva-renews-its-commitment-towards-agrobiodiversity-alongside-the-fondation-du-patrimoine/|title=Ceva committed to agrobiodiversity alongside the Fondation du Patrimoine|last=read|first=Healthy Planet\u00b71 min|date=2019-02-11|website=Together Beyond Animal Health|access-date=2019-03-20}}</ref>\n\nCeva has supported TOLFA (Tree of Life for Animals), an animal welfare charity registered in the UK and India with its operational base in Rajasthan, Northern India. Rachel Wright, TOLFA's founder, was recognised as the Welfare Nurse of the Year in the inaugural Ceva Awards for Animal Welfare.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vettimes.co.uk/news/ceva-awards-for-animal-welfare-winners-announced/|title=Ceva Awards for Animal Welfare: Winners announced|last=Times|first=Vet|date=2012-04-13|website=Vet Times|access-date=2019-03-20}}</ref>\n\n== Business with blood farms ==\nCeva has funded several studies about the [[equine chorionic gonadotropin]] (eCG) effects on livestock productivity<ref>{{Cite web|title=Proceedings of the 30th Annual Meeting of the Brazilian Embryo Technology Society (SBTE)|url=http://www.cbra.org.br/pages/publicacoes/animalreproduction/issues/download/v13/v13n3/p375-461(FTAI,%20FTET%20and%20AI)-%20SBTE.pdf|website=cbra.org.br|year=2016}}.</ref><ref>{{Cite book|lang=fr-FR|author=Agathe Jonckeau|title=Production, purification et caract\u00e9risation d'une gonadotropine chorionique \u00e9quine recombinante \u00e0 usage v\u00e9t\u00e9rinaire|place=Bordeaux|date=2016-12-15|url=http://www.theses.fr/2016BORD0208|access-date=2019-06-04|publisher=Bordeaux}}.</ref>, including one at [[\u00c9cole nationale v\u00e9t\u00e9rinaire d'Alfort]], 2001.<ref>http://theses.vet-alfort.fr/telecharger.php?id=284</ref> According to an investigation published in French journal ''[[Lib\u00e9ration]]'', CEVA bought the eCG in [[Syntex]] bloodfarms<ref name=\"Lib\u00e9\">{{Cite journal|lang=fr-FR|author=Sarah Finger|title=Des juments saign\u00e9es aux quatre veines pour l'\u00e9levage fran\u00e7ais|journal=[[Lib\u00e9ration]]|date=2017-10-05|issn=|url=http://www.liberation.fr/france/2017/10/05/des-juments-saignees-aux-quatre-veines---pour-l-elevage-francais_1601168|access-date=2017-10-08}}.</ref>, accused of cruelty to animals by NGOs Eyes on Animals (Netherlands)<ref name=\"EyesonAnimals\">{{Cite web|lang=nl|title=Paarden mishandeld voor hormoonmiddelen Nederlandse vee-industrie|url=https://www.eyesonanimals.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Paarden-mishandeld-voor-hormoonmiddelen-Nederlandse-vee-industrie-persbericht-EonA-05.12.2015.pdf|website=eyesonanimals.com|place=Amsterdam|date=2015-11-05}}.</ref>, Tierschutzbund Zurich (TSB - Switzerland ), Animal Welfare Foundation (AWF - Germany)<ref>{{Cite journal|lang=fr-FR|author=Patricia Jolly|title=Le triste sort des juments \u00e9lev\u00e9es pour leur sang \" jusqu'\u00e0 l'\u00e9puisement \"|journal=[[Le Monde]]|date=2017-10-06|issn=1950-6244|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/planete/article/2017/10/06/le-triste-sort-des-juments-elevees-pour-leur-sang-jusqu-a-l-epuisement_5197458_3244.html|access-date=2017-10-08}}.</ref><ref name=\"Lib\u00e9\"/> and Welfarm (France)<ref name=\"welf\">{{Cite web|lang=en|title=Welfarm.fr - Actualit\u00e9s|url=https://welfarm.fr/news/554/86/Nouvelle-vid%C3%A9o-dans-lenfer-des-fermes-%C3%A0-sang|website=welfarm.fr|access-date=2018-07-23}}.</ref>, among others.\n\nPierre Revel-Mouroz, Deputy Chief Executive Officer in charge of the audit at Ceva Sant\u00e9 Animale, alerted in 2015, justified this choice by \"the absence of detection of anomalies in the farm where the laboratory gets supplies\".<ref name=\"FranceTV\">{{Cite web|lang=fr-FR|title=Am\u00e9rique du Sud : des juments f\u00e9cond\u00e9es et avort\u00e9es \u00e0 vif plusieurs fois dans l'ann\u00e9e pour des pr\u00e9l\u00e8vements de sang|website=Franceinfo|date=2017-10-06|url=https://www.francetvinfo.fr/animaux/bien-etre-animal/amerique-du-sud-des-juments-fecondees-et-avortees-a-vif-plusieurs-fois-dans-l-annee-pour-des-prelevements-de-sang_2406399.html|access-date=2017-10-16}}.</ref><ref name=\"Lib\u00e9\"/> According to ''Lib\u00e9ration'', Ceva continued to supply from Syntex mid-July 2018, despite repeated warnings: the article denounces this \"inertia\"<ref>{{Cite journal|lang=fr-FR|author=Sarah Finger|title=Juments saign\u00e9es et avort\u00e9es : l'inertie coupable des laboratoires fran\u00e7ais|journal=Lib\u00e9ration|date=2018-07-17|issn=|url=http://www.liberation.fr/france/2018/07/17/juments-saignees-et-avortees-l-inertie-coupable-des-laboratoires-francais_1667173|access-date=2018-07-22}}.</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|lang=fr-FR|title=Souffrance animale : le scandale des \"fermes \u00e0 sang\"|journal=Franceinfo|date=2018-07-18|url=https://www.francetvinfo.fr/monde/ameriques/souffrance-animale-le-scandale-des-fermes-a-sang_2856097.html|access-date=2018-07-23}}.</ref>. On July 25, 2018, Ceva announced an investigation to verify the quality of life of the concerned mares.<ref>{{Cite web|lang=fr|title=Scandale des fermes \u00e0 -sang : CEVA prend position|url=http://www.grandprix-replay.com/be/new/10838/scandale-des-fermes-a-sang-ceva-prend-position|website=[[Grand Prix magazine]]|date=2018-07-25|access-date=2018-08-07}}.</ref> On August 3, 2018, the laboratory indicates (on its website) to renounce to provide in South America.<ref>{{Cite web|lang=fr|title=Ceva renonce au sang de juments d'Am\u00e9rique du Sud|url=https://welfarm.fr/news/556/86/Ceva-renonce-au-sang-de-juments-dAm%C3%A9rique-du-Sud|website=welfarm.fr|date=2018-08-06|access-date=2018-08-07}}.</ref><ref>{{Cite web|lang=fr|title=Ceva renonce \u00e0 l'eCG d'Am\u00e9rique latine|url=https://www.depecheveterinaire.com/ceva-renonce-a-l-ecg-d-amerique-latine_679A4E833572B3.html|website=La d\u00e9p\u00eache V\u00e9t\u00e9rinaire|date=2018-04-10|access-date=2019-06-04}}.</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eurogroupforanimals.org/animal-welfare-foundation-and-tierschutzbund-zurich-ceva-and-idt-biologika-will-stop-sourcing-pmsg-ecg-from-blood-farms-where-mares-are-still-systematically-tortured|title=ANIMAL WELFARE FOUNDATION AND TIERSCHUTZBUND Z\u00dcRICH: CEVA AND IDT BIOLOGIKA WILL STOP SOURCING PMSG-ECG FROM BLOOD FARMS WHERE MARES ARE STILL SYSTEMATICALLY TORTURED Blood Farms, PMSG, South America, Animal Welfare Foundation|website=www.eurogroupforanimals.org|date=2018-08-29|access-date=2019-10-23}}.</ref> On 16 December 2018, the collectif Boucherie Abolition published an article accusing the multinational CEVA of \"zoocide\".<ref>{{Cite web|lang=fr-FR|title=CEVA : la multinationale v\u00e9t\u00e9rinaire qui orchestre un zoocide mondial|url=https://boucherie-abolition.com/2018/12/16/ceva-la-multinationale-veterinaire-qui-orchestre-un-zoocide-mondial/|website=Boucherie Abolition|date=2018-12-16|access-date=2019-06-04}}.</ref>\n\nThe concerned products are marketed as \"Fertipig\" for pigs, and \"Syncro Part\" or \"Syncrostim\" for cattle.\n\n== References ==\n<!-- Inline citations added to your article will automatically display here. See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WP:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. -->\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Veterinary companies]]\n[[Category:Companies of France]]\n[[Category:1999 establishments in France]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company\n| name = Ceva Sant\u00e9 Animale\n| logo = \n| type = \n| industry = [[Veterinary medicine]]\n| fate = \n| predecessors = [[Sanofi]]<br> Synth\u00e9labo\n| successor = <!-- or: | successors = -->\n| founded = {{Start date and age|1999}}\n| founder = <!-- or: | founders = -->\n| defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| hq_location_city = [[Libourne]]\n| hq_location_country = France\n| area_served = <!-- or: | areas_served = -->\n| key_people = Marc Prikazsky ([[CEO]] & [[Chairman]])\n| products = \n| owner = <!-- or: | owners = -->\n| num_employees = 5,700\n| num_employees_year = \n| parent = \n| website = {{URL|ceva.com/en}}\n}}\n'''Ceva Sant\u00e9 Animale''' (Ceva) is a multinational animal health company based in [[Libourne]], France. Established in 1999, Ceva undertakes research, development, production and marketing of pharmaceutical products and vaccines, and also provides complementary services and equipment, for companion animals, poultry, ruminants and swine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thepoultrysite.com/poultrynews/39902/ceva-launches-a-new-wave-of-innovation-to-help-poultry-producers-meet-the-performance-challenges-driven-by-the-need-for-no-antibiotics-and-more-sustainable-production/|title=Ceva launches a \"new wave of innovation\" to help poultry producers meet the performance challenges driven by the need for \"No antibiotics\" and more sustainable production|website=The Poultry Site|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref>\n\nCeva also supplies; hatchery vaccines, vaccination services and equipment; pheromone-based behavioural products for cats and dogs with additional knowledge in companion animal cardiology, locomotion and dermatology; products for the management of reproduction in ruminants such as antibiotic therapies and vaccines; and a growing range of products for swine, including antibiotic therapies, reproduction management and vaccines.\n\nWith revenues of US$1.16 billion (\u20ac1.1 billion) for 2017, Ceva is the 6th largest animal health company in the world and the biggest French multinational in the sector based on revenue.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.statista.com/statistics/260190/leading-animal-health-providers-based-on-revenue/|title=Top animal health companies by revenue worldwide 2017 {{!}} Statistic|website=Statista|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref>\n\nCeva is based in 45 countries and works in more than 110 countries worldwide. It has 12 research and development centres, 25 production sites and more than 5,500 employees.\n\nIn 2010, to mark its 10<sup>th</sup> anniversary, the company adopted a new mission statement, \u2018Together, we are building a new reference to create value beyond animal health\u2019, abbreviated in the slogan to \u2018Together, beyond animal health\u2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://animalpharm.agribusinessintelligence.informa.com/AP005120/Ceva---Together-beyond-animal-health|title=Ceva - 'Together beyond animal health'|date=2010-11-26|website=Animal Pharm|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nThe Chairman and CEO is Marc Prikazsky.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/tosv2.html?vid=&uuid=d4260350-2e16-11e9-8043-9b0a5f1e26ed&url=L3Jlc2VhcmNoL3N0b2Nrcy9wcml2YXRlL3BlcnNvbi5hc3A/cGVyc29uSWQ9NDI3NDI2ODQmcHJpdmNhcElkPTEzNTU3OSZwcmV2aW91c0NhcElkPTE5MTE1JnByZXZpb3VzVGl0bGU9QkMlMjUyNTI1MjBQYXJ0bmVycw==|title=Bloomberg - Are you a robot?|website=www.bloomberg.com|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nCeva is accused of participating in serious treatment of [[Mare|mares]] to provide [[equine chorionic gonadotropin]].\n\n== History ==\nIn 1999, two French pharmaceutical companies, [[Sanofi]] and Synth\u00e9labo, merged to form Sanofi-Synth\u00e9labo. Soon after the merger, the new company divested several businesses, including its animal health and nutrition business, Sanofi Sant\u00e9 Nutrition Animale.\n\nThis business was acquired through the first of four [[Leveraged buyout|leveraged management buyouts]] (LMBO) and resulted in the establishment in 1999 of Ceva Sant\u00e9 Animal. Following the third LMBO, in 2007 Ceva management and employees acquired the majority shareholding in the company.\n\nIn 2014, there was a Reshaping of Ceva's capital structure to accompany the launch of the company's ambition to become the first independent player within the top 5 global animal health companies by 2020. While management still retained the position of majority shareholders long-term strategic partners were selected to support the group's future growth ambitions:[[Temasek Holdings|Temasek]], [[CDH Investments]], Euromezzanine, [[About:blank|Sagard]] and M\u00e9rieux D\u00e9veloppement.\n\nSince 1999, Ceva has been the sole shareholder of Ceva-Phylaxia. Founded in Hungary in 1912, the Phylaxia Vaccine Production Co produced the first vaccine against [[classical swine fever]]. Scientists including [[J\u00f3zsef Marek]] and [[Alad\u00e1r Aujeszky]] were closely associated with the company. \n\nCeva has grown rapidly through both acquisitions and organic growth. In 2000 it ranked 18<sup>th</sup> globally with sales of US$140 million a year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://animalpharm.agribusinessintelligence.informa.com/AP012786/A-carousel-of-companies-Inside-the-industry-consolidation-of-19902000|title=A carousel of companies: Inside the industry consolidation of 1990-2000|date=2017-08-03|website=Animal Pharm|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\n'''Major acquisitions by Ceva include:''' \n\n* 2017: Purchase of ex-Merial product range<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://animalpharm.agribusinessintelligence.informa.com/AP011375/Ceva-closes-acquisition-of-Merial-assets|title=Ceva closes acquisition of Merial assets|date=2017-01-19|website=Animal Pharm|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n* 2017: Joint-venture agreement between EBVAC, China and Ceva to create a new business, Ceva Ebvac, focused on the swine vaccine sector\n* 2016: Hertape Saude Animale Ltda. and Inova Biotecnologia Saude Animale Ltda, Brazil, \n* 2016: Biovac, a manufacturer of autogeneous (bacterial) vaccines, allergy treatments and reagents based in Angers, France<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://objectifaquitaine.latribune.fr/business/2016-06-02/ceva-sante-animale-acquiert-le-laboratoire-biovac.html|title=Ceva Sant\u00e9 animale acquiert le laboratoire Biovac|website=La Tribune|language=fr|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n* 2015: Polchem, India<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20160308006326/en/Ceva-Reports-Annual-Growth-12-Reaffirms-Ambition|title=Ceva Reports Annual Growth of 12% and Reaffirms Ambition to Enter the Global Top 5 by 2020|date=2016-03-08|website=www.businesswire.com|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n* 2013: Sogeval \n* 2011: Vetech Laboratories, Inc., a Canadian poultry vaccine manufacturer that produces live coccidiosis vaccines for poultry under the trade name Immucox\u00ae \n* 2011: First joint venture established in China, Ceva Huadu\n* 2010: Summit VetPharm, a New Jersey-based company\n* 2005: Biomune, a US poultry vaccine producer based in [[Lenexa, Kansas|Lenexa]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kclifesciences.org/news/life-sciences-bulletin/volume-1-2014/ceva-going-beyond-animal-health/|title=Ceva: Going Beyond Animal Health {{!}} Kansas City Area Life Sciences Institute|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and recognition ==\nIn 2016, Ceva won the best company in Europe category in Animal Pharm's annual industry awards.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pig333.com/company_news/ceva-best-company-in-europe-winner-animal-pharm-awards-2016_12105/|title=Ceva: Best Company in Europe winner Animal Pharm awards 2016|website=www.pig333.com|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Ceva's hatchery vaccination services program for poultry, the C.H.I.C.K Program, received quality recognition from the international testing and certification company, Bureau Veritas Group, based in Paris. This was the first time a services program delivered by an animal health company had received internationally recognised quality approval.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thepoultrysite.com/focus/ceva/2790/ceva-hatchery-services-chick-program|title=Ceva - Hatchery Services - C.H.I.C.K. Program|website=The Poultry Site|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nSince 2005, Ceva has been awarded six International Cat Care (ICC) Easy to Give Awards. It has also received three ICC Cat Friendly Awards for products in the [[Cat pheromone|Feliway]] range. The Cat Friendly Awards recognise products which have made a real difference to cat wellbeing and welfare.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://icatcare.org/about-us/awards|title=Our awards {{!}} International Cat Care|website=icatcare.org|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\n== Key partnerships ==\nCeva established a partnership with the l\u2019Association Chiens Guides d'Aveugles Ali\u00e9nor (guide dogs for the blind association).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chiensguides-alienor.com/|title=Ecole de chiens guides Ali\u00e9nor-Sud-Ouest|website=www.chiensguides-alienor.com|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\n'''2018'''\n\nCeva is associated with the [[Union Bordeaux B\u00e8gles]], a French rugby union team. The team's new performance centre, inaugurated in October at the Moga stadium in B\u00e8gles, has been named the Ceva Campus.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sudouest.fr/2018/10/04/-5446383-4583.php|title=L'UBB dispose d'un bel outil|website=SudOuest.fr|language=fr-FR|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nWageningen Bioveterinary Research (WBVR) and Ceva are developing veterinary vaccines for the control of (re)emerging infectious animal diseases, such as Rift Valley fever and Influenza.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thepoultrysite.com/poultrynews/40117/wageningen-bioveterinary-research-and-ceva-form-strategic-alliance-to-counter-global-threat-of-emerging-and-reemerging-diseases/|title=Wageningen Bioveterinary Research and Ceva form strategic alliance to counter global threat of emerging and re-emerging diseases|website=The Poultry Site|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nThe North Carolina State College of Veterinary Medicine and Ceva are collaborating on a distance learning project providing certification in poultry health management for veterinarians in Latin America.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thepoultrysite.com/poultrynews/39785/cvm-and-ceva-enter-educational-partnership-for-latin-american-veterinarians/|title=CVM and Ceva enter educational partnership for Latin American veterinarians|website=The Poultry Site|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\n'''2017'''\n\n[[World Veterinary Association|The World Veterinary Association]] (WVA) created the Global Animal Welfare Awards, co-founded and supported by Ceva, to recognize and reward veterinarians who contribute to the protection and welfare of animals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldvet.org/news.php?item=322|title=WVA News|website=www.worldvet.org|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nThe World Veterinary Poultry Association (WVPA) and Ceva launched a digital library resource on poultry veterinary medicine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wvpa.net/library.php|title=WVPA|website=www.wvpa.net|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\n'''2015'''\n\nCeva is involved in a program to supply Australia's wildlife veterinarians with an antibiotic to treat [[Chlamydia infection|chlamydia]] disease in koala's free of charge.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fiercepharma.com/r-d/ceva-combats-chlamydia-australian-koalas-new-program|title=Ceva combats chlamydia in Australian koalas with new program {{!}} FiercePharma|website=www.fiercepharma.com|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nCeva partnered with WikiVet to develop a comprehensive on-line peer reviewed veterinary knowledge database and add a module on feline behaviour.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.wikivet.net/Feline_Behaviour|title=Feline Behaviour - WikiVet English|website=en.wikivet.net|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nCeva received a grant from the [[Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation]] to improve the lives of smallholder and poor village farmers by improving the health and productive capacity of poultry and cattle, species with significant economic importance to poor livestock keepers in developing countries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gatesfoundation.org/How-We-Work/Quick-Links/Grants-Database/Grants/2015/11/OPP1134139|title=OPP1134139|website=Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref>\n\nCeva sponsored the UK Animal Welfare Awards, in partnership with the Veterinary Times and the VN Times.\n\n'''2012'''\n\nSince 2012, the Fondation du Patrimoine and Ceva, under the patronage of the French Ministry of Agriculture, have awarded the Fondation du Patrimoine National Animal Agro-Biodiversity Prize in recognition of initiatives to preserve and promote French rare breeds.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.togetherbeyondanimalhealth.com/ceva-renews-its-commitment-towards-agrobiodiversity-alongside-the-fondation-du-patrimoine/|title=Ceva committed to agrobiodiversity alongside the Fondation du Patrimoine|last=read|first=Healthy Planet\u00b71 min|date=2019-02-11|website=Together Beyond Animal Health|access-date=2019-03-20}}</ref>\n\nCeva has supported TOLFA (Tree of Life for Animals), an animal welfare charity registered in the UK and India with its operational base in Rajasthan, Northern India. Rachel Wright, TOLFA's founder, was recognised as the Welfare Nurse of the Year in the inaugural Ceva Awards for Animal Welfare.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vettimes.co.uk/news/ceva-awards-for-animal-welfare-winners-announced/|title=Ceva Awards for Animal Welfare: Winners announced|last=Times|first=Vet|date=2012-04-13|website=Vet Times|access-date=2019-03-20}}</ref>\n\n== Business with blood farms ==\nCeva has funded several studies about the [[equine chorionic gonadotropin]] (eCG) effects on livestock productivity<ref>{{Cite web|title=Proceedings of the 30th Annual Meeting of the Brazilian Embryo Technology Society (SBTE)|url=http://www.cbra.org.br/pages/publicacoes/animalreproduction/issues/download/v13/v13n3/p375-461(FTAI,%20FTET%20and%20AI)-%20SBTE.pdf|website=cbra.org.br|year=2016}}.</ref><ref>{{Cite book|lang=fr-FR|author=Agathe Jonckeau|title=Production, purification et caract\u00e9risation d'une gonadotropine chorionique \u00e9quine recombinante \u00e0 usage v\u00e9t\u00e9rinaire|place=Bordeaux|date=2016-12-15|url=http://www.theses.fr/2016BORD0208|access-date=2019-06-04|publisher=Bordeaux}}.</ref>, including one at [[\u00c9cole nationale v\u00e9t\u00e9rinaire d'Alfort]], 2001.<ref>http://theses.vet-alfort.fr/telecharger.php?id=284</ref> According to an investigation published in French journal ''[[Lib\u00e9ration]]'', CEVA bought the eCG in [[Syntex]] bloodfarms<ref name=\"Lib\u00e9\">{{Cite journal|lang=fr-FR|author=Sarah Finger|title=Des juments saign\u00e9es aux quatre veines pour\u00a0l'\u00e9levage fran\u00e7ais|journal=[[Lib\u00e9ration]]|date=2017-10-05|issn=|url=http://www.liberation.fr/france/2017/10/05/des-juments-saignees-aux-quatre-veines---pour-l-elevage-francais_1601168|access-date=2017-10-08}}.</ref>, accused of cruelty to animals by NGOs Eyes on Animals (Netherlands)<ref name=\"EyesonAnimals\">{{Cite web|lang=nl|title=Paarden mishandeld voor hormoonmiddelen Nederlandse vee-industrie|url=https://www.eyesonanimals.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Paarden-mishandeld-voor-hormoonmiddelen-Nederlandse-vee-industrie-persbericht-EonA-05.12.2015.pdf|website=eyesonanimals.com|place=Amsterdam|date=2015-11-05}}.</ref>, Tierschutzbund Zurich (TSB - Switzerland ), Animal Welfare Foundation (AWF - Germany)<ref>{{Cite journal|lang=fr-FR|author=Patricia Jolly|title=Le triste sort des juments \u00e9lev\u00e9es pour leur sang \" jusqu'\u00e0 l'\u00e9puisement \"|journal=[[Le Monde]]|date=2017-10-06|issn=1950-6244|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/planete/article/2017/10/06/le-triste-sort-des-juments-elevees-pour-leur-sang-jusqu-a-l-epuisement_5197458_3244.html|access-date=2017-10-08}}.</ref><ref name=\"Lib\u00e9\"/> and Welfarm (France)<ref name=\"welf\">{{Cite web|lang=en|title=Welfarm.fr - Actualit\u00e9s|url=https://welfarm.fr/news/554/86/Nouvelle-vid%C3%A9o-dans-lenfer-des-fermes-%C3%A0-sang|website=welfarm.fr|access-date=2018-07-23}}.</ref>, among others.\n\nPierre Revel-Mouroz, Deputy Chief Executive Officer in charge of the audit at Ceva Sant\u00e9 Animale, alerted in 2015, justified this choice by \"the absence of detection of anomalies in the farm where the laboratory gets supplies\".<ref name=\"FranceTV\">{{Cite web|lang=fr-FR|title=Am\u00e9rique du Sud : des juments f\u00e9cond\u00e9es et avort\u00e9es \u00e0 vif plusieurs fois dans l'ann\u00e9e pour des pr\u00e9l\u00e8vements de sang|website=Franceinfo|date=2017-10-06|url=https://www.francetvinfo.fr/animaux/bien-etre-animal/amerique-du-sud-des-juments-fecondees-et-avortees-a-vif-plusieurs-fois-dans-l-annee-pour-des-prelevements-de-sang_2406399.html|access-date=2017-10-16}}.</ref><ref name=\"Lib\u00e9\"/> According to ''Lib\u00e9ration'', Ceva continued to supply from Syntex mid-July 2018, despite repeated warnings: the article denounces this \"inertia\"<ref>{{Cite journal|lang=fr-FR|author=Sarah Finger|title=Juments saign\u00e9es et avort\u00e9es\u00a0: l'inertie coupable des laboratoires fran\u00e7ais|journal=Lib\u00e9ration|date=2018-07-17|issn=|url=http://www.liberation.fr/france/2018/07/17/juments-saignees-et-avortees-l-inertie-coupable-des-laboratoires-francais_1667173|access-date=2018-07-22}}.</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|lang=fr-FR|title=Souffrance animale : le scandale des \"fermes \u00e0 sang\"|journal=Franceinfo|date=2018-07-18|url=https://www.francetvinfo.fr/monde/ameriques/souffrance-animale-le-scandale-des-fermes-a-sang_2856097.html|access-date=2018-07-23}}.</ref>. On July 25, 2018, Ceva announced an investigation to verify the quality of life of the concerned mares.<ref>{{Cite web|lang=fr|title=Scandale des fermes \u00e0 -sang : CEVA prend position|url=http://www.grandprix-replay.com/be/new/10838/scandale-des-fermes-a-sang-ceva-prend-position|website=[[Grand Prix magazine]]|date=2018-07-25|access-date=2018-08-07}}.</ref> On August 3, 2018, the laboratory indicates (on its website) to renounce to provide in South America.<ref>{{Cite web|lang=fr|title=Ceva renonce au sang de juments d'Am\u00e9rique du Sud|url=https://welfarm.fr/news/556/86/Ceva-renonce-au-sang-de-juments-dAm%C3%A9rique-du-Sud|website=welfarm.fr|date=2018-08-06|access-date=2018-08-07}}.</ref><ref>{{Cite web|lang=fr|title=Ceva renonce \u00e0 l'eCG d'Am\u00e9rique latine|url=https://www.depecheveterinaire.com/ceva-renonce-a-l-ecg-d-amerique-latine_679A4E833572B3.html|website=La d\u00e9p\u00eache V\u00e9t\u00e9rinaire|date=2018-04-10|access-date=2019-06-04}}.</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eurogroupforanimals.org/animal-welfare-foundation-and-tierschutzbund-zurich-ceva-and-idt-biologika-will-stop-sourcing-pmsg-ecg-from-blood-farms-where-mares-are-still-systematically-tortured|title=ANIMAL WELFARE FOUNDATION AND TIERSCHUTZBUND Z\u00dcRICH: CEVA AND IDT BIOLOGIKA WILL STOP SOURCING PMSG-ECG FROM BLOOD FARMS WHERE MARES ARE STILL SYSTEMATICALLY TORTURED Blood Farms, PMSG, South America, Animal Welfare Foundation|website=www.eurogroupforanimals.org|date=2018-08-29|access-date=2019-10-23}}.</ref> On 16 December 2018, the collectif Boucherie Abolition published an article accusing the multinational CEVA of \"zoocide\".<ref>{{Cite web|lang=fr-FR|title=CEVA : la multinationale v\u00e9t\u00e9rinaire qui orchestre un zoocide mondial|url=https://boucherie-abolition.com/2018/12/16/ceva-la-multinationale-veterinaire-qui-orchestre-un-zoocide-mondial/|website=Boucherie Abolition|date=2018-12-16|access-date=2019-06-04}}.</ref>\n\nThe concerned products are marketed as \"Fertipig\" for pigs, and \"Syncro Part\" or \"Syncrostim\" for cattle.\n\n== References ==\n<!-- Inline citations added to your article will automatically display here. See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WP:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. -->\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Veterinary companies]]\n[[Category:Companies of France]]\n[[Category:1999 establishments in France]]\n", "name_user": "DferDaisy", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBusiness with blood farms:removed no-break space characters causing template error in references", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ceva_Sant%C3%A9_Animale"}
{"title_page": "Sakura Miyawaki", "text_new": "{{Short description|Japanese singer}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Sakura Miyawaki\n| image              = Sakura Miyawaki at Music Bank on April 12, 2019.png<!--Please do not change without providing a reason -->\n| alt                = \n| caption            = Miyawaki at Music Bank in April 2019\n| native_name        = \u5bae\u8107 \u54b2\u826f\n| native_name_lang   = ja\n| birth_name         = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1998|3|19|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Kagoshima]], Japan\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| residence          = \n| alias              = Kura,Sakuchan,Saachan \n| occupation         = Singer, actress\n| years_active       = 2011<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nuts-pro.com/cgi-bin/info_view.cgi|title=WHATS NEW -NUTS PRODUCTION-|date=January 13, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140113014205/http://www.nuts-pro.com/cgi-bin/info_view.cgi|archive-date=2014-01-13}}</ref>\u2013present\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist\n| embed           = yes <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| background      = solo_singer\n| genre           = {{flatlist|\n* [[J-pop]]\n* [[K-pop]]}}\n| instrument      = Vocals\n| label           = {{flatlist|\n* [[AKS (company)|AKS]]\n* Off The Record   \n}}\n| associated_acts = {{hlist|[[HKT48]]|[[AKB48]]|[[Iz*One]]|}}\n}}\n| module2            = {{Infobox YouTube personality|embed=yes\n| channel_url         = https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC9Z0cgZPBa2szfjcrJdfYvA\n| channel_display_name = Channel Sakura Miyawaki\n| years_active      = 2018~present\n| genre             = [[Video game|Gaming]]\n| subscribers       = 516,000\n| subscriber_date   = April 2, 2020\n| views             = 14,780,958\n| view_date         = April 2, 2020\n| silver_button     = yes\n| silver_year       = 2018\n}}\n| module3            = {{Infobox Chinese | child= yes\n| kanji             = \u5bae\u8107 \u54b2\u826f\n| romaji            = Miyawaki Sakura\n| hiragana          = \u307f\u3084\u308f\u304d \u3055\u304f\u3089\n| katakana          = \u30df\u30e4\u30ef\u30ad \u30b5\u30af\u30e9\n}}\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Sakura Miyawaki'''|\u5bae\u8107 \u54b2\u826f|Miyawaki Sakura|born 19 March 1998}} is a Japanese singer and actress. She is a member of the Japanese [[Japanese idol|idol]] girl group [[HKT48]] and was a part of [[AKB48]] Team A , she was known as the post [[Maeda Atsuko]] and was said to be the next Ace of the 48 group.She acted  as one of the main characters in the drama \"[[Majisuka Gakuen]]\" and was also the main character for [[Crow's Blood]] and [[Tofu Pro Wrestling]] . She became a member of Japanese-South Korean girl group [[Iz*One]] after finishing second in survival reality television show ''[[Produce 48]]''  in 2018. \n\nIn the General Elections of [[AKB48]], she has placed 47th (2012), 26th (2013), 11th (2014), 7th (2015), 6th (2016), 4th (2017), and 3rd (2018).\n\nAs one of the group's leading members, Miyawaki became the center (leading singer and dancer) of AKB48's 43rd single \"[[Kimi wa Melody]]\" (Your Melody) which is also AKB48's 10th Anniversary Memorial single in January 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tokyogirlsupdate.com/sakura-akb48-43rd-kimi-wa-melody-20160176740.html|title=AKB48's 43rd Single \"Kimi wa Melody\" Revealed on Final Day of Request Hour 2016!|website=Japanese kawaii idol music culture news {{!}} Tokyo Girls Update|access-date=2016-04-16}}</ref> In 2017, together with [[Jurina Matsui]] from SKE48, the two next generation aces that are also known as \"JuriSaku\" were chosen to be the WCenter (double centers) for AKB48 group commemorative 48th single \"[[Negaigoto no Mochigusare]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jpopasia.com/feed/20951/akb48-announces-9th-senbatsu-general-election-48th-single|work=J-pop Asia|title=AKB48 Announces 9th Senbatsu General Election + 48th Single|date=March 20, 2017|accessdate=March 20, 2019|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Miyawaki joined the show ''[[Produce 48]]'' and was selected as the center of the show's theme song, \"[[Nekkoya (Pick Me)|Nekkoya]]\". She placed 2nd and debuted on October 29, 2018 as a member of [[Iz*One]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=241&aid=0002776907|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5]\ubbf8\uc57c\uc640\ud0a4 \uc0ac\ucfe0\ub77c, '\ud504\ub85c\ub4c0\uc2a4 48' \uc13c\ud130\ub410\ub2e4|last=|first=|date=|work=Naver|access-date=|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nMiyawaki joined [[HKT48]] as a first generation trainee in July 2011. She made her first official appearance as an HKT48 member on October 23 at a national handshake event for the song \"[[Flying Get]]\". She made her theater debut on November 26 with a revival of [[SKE48]] Team S stage \"Te wo Tsunaginagara\".<ref>{{cite news|title=HKT48\u3001\u5730\u5143\u535a\u591a\u3067\u300c\u624b\u3092\u3064\u306a\u304e\u306a\u304c\u3089\u300d\u516c\u6f14\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc\u30c8|author=|url=http://news.nicovideo.jp/watch/nw152778|work=Natalie Music|date=November 11, 2011|accessdate=March 20, 2019|language=ja}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/music/2002974/full/ |title=HKT48\u3001\u897f\u6b66\u30c9\u30fc\u30e0\u3067\u521d\u4ee321\u4eba\u304a\u62ab\u9732\u76ee\u3000AKB\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u6700\u5e74\u5c11\u306e\u5e73\u5747\u5e74\u9f6213.8\u6b73 |date=October 23, 2011|accessdate=March 20, 2019|work=Oricon, Inc. |language=Ja}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.tokyohive.com/2011/11/hkt48-makes-their-theater-debut/ |title=HKT48 makes their theater debut|date=November 27, 2011|accessdate=March 20, 2019|work=Tokyohive|language=en}}</ref>\n\nMiyawaki was officially promoted to full member status of HKT48 Team H on March 4, 2012, along with 15 other trainees.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://ameblo.jp/hkt48/entry-11181717875.html|title=HKT48 \u30c1\u30fc\u30e0\uff28\u304a\u62ab\u9732\u76ee\u516c\u6f14\u7d42\u4e86|date=March 4, 2012 |accessdate=March 20, 2019|work= HKT48 official blog|language=Ja}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tokyohive.com/article/2012/03/hkt48-introduces-the-members-of-team-h|title=HKT48 introduces the members of 'Team H'|date=November 27, 2011|accessdate=March 20, 2019|work=Tokyohive|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, Miyawaki became the first HKT48 member  to have ranked in the AKB48 general election. She received 6,635 votes, placing her at the 47th position.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://japan.techinsight.jp/2012/06/hktmiyawaki-senbatu-rkb20120610.html|title=\u3010\u30a8\u30f3\u30bf\u304c\u30d3\u30bf\u30df\u30f3\u266a\u3011\u300c\u982d\u304c\u771f\u3063\u767d\u306b\u306a\u3063\u305f\u300d\u3002AKB\u9078\u629c\u7dcf\u9078\u631947\u4f4d\u3002HKT48\u5bae\u8107\u54b2\u826f\u304c\u751f\u653e\u9001\u3067\u5fc3\u5883\u8a9e\u308b\u3002|date=June 11, 2012|website=Techinsight\uff08\u30c6\u30c3\u30af\u30a4\u30f3\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8\uff09&#124;\u6d77\u5916\u30bb\u30ec\u30d6\u3001\u56fd\u5185\u30a8\u30f3\u30bf\u30e1\u306e\u30aa\u30f3\u30ea\u30fc\u30ef\u30f3\u3092\u304a\u5c4a\u3051\u3059\u308b\u30cb\u30e5\u30fc\u30b9\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8}}</ref> Later that year, she landed her first A-side participation on AKB48's 28th single \"[[Uza (song)|Uza]]\". Although she did not make the A-side for the 29th and 30th singles, she appeared on the A-side for the 31st single, \"[[Sayonara Crawl]]\", released on May 22, 2013, and placed 26th overall in AKB48's 2013 general election with 25,760 votes.<ref name=\"election2013\">{{cite web|url=http://www.akb48.co.jp/sousenkyo/32ndsingle/result.php|title = AKB48 32nd\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb \u9078\u629c\u7dcf\u9078\u6319 |trans-title=32nd single selection elections | work = AKB48 Official Site | date = 2013-06-08 | language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nMiyawaki's first A-side participation with HKT48 was on its first single \"[[Suki! Suki! Skip!]]\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hkt48.jp/discography/single/006115.html|title=\u30c7\u30a3\u30b9\u30b3\u30b0\u30e9\u30d5\u30a3\u30fc - \u30b9\u30ad\uff01\u30b9\u30ad\uff01\u30b9\u30ad\u30c3\u30d7\uff01|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130814111225/http://www.hkt48.jp/discography/single/006115.html|archive-date=2013-08-14|df=}}</ref> (Like! Like! Skip!) and [[Melon Juice (HKT48 song)|Melon Juice]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hkt48.jp/discography/single/007474.html|title=\u30c7\u30a3\u30b9\u30b3\u30b0\u30e9\u30d5\u30a3\u30fc - \u30e1\u30ed\u30f3\u30b8\u30e5\u30fc\u30b9|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140220151822/http://www.hkt48.jp/discography/single/007474.html|archive-date=2014-02-20|df=}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 January 2014, it was announced during the first day of [[HKT48]]'s Kyushu 7 Prefecture Tour at Oita, that Miyawaki would be transferred to the newly formed Team KIV.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2032880/full/|title=HKT48\u3001\u65b0\u30c1\u30fc\u30e0\u300cKIV\u300d\u767a\u8db3\uff06\u521d\u518d\u7de8 \u6307\u539f\u5287\u5834\u652f\u914d\u4eba\u304c\"\u30af\u30e9\u30b9\u66ff\u3048\"\u767a\u8868|website=ORICON NEWS}}</ref> Later, at AKB48's Group Grand Reformation Festival, she was promoted to vice captain of Team KIV and given a concurrent position in AKB48 Team A.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://realsound.jp/2014/02/akb48ske48nmb4846.html|title=AKB48\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u300c\u5927\u7d44\u95a3\u796d\u308a\u300d\u901f\u5831 \u4e43\u6728\u574246\u751f\u99d2\u3001SKE48\u6728\u5d0e\u306a\u3069\u306e\u4ef0\u5929\u4eba\u4e8b\u3082\u7d9a\u3005|website=Real Sound\uff5c\u30ea\u30a2\u30eb\u30b5\u30a6\u30f3\u30c9}}</ref>\n\nMiyawaki participated in the 2014 AKB48 general election and placed 11th overall with 45,538 votes, landing her a position on the A-side for \"[[Kokoro no Placard]]\".<ref name=\"election2014\">{{cite web|url=http://www.akb48.co.jp/sousenkyo/37thsingle/result.php|title = AKB48 37th\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb \u9078\u629c\u7dcf\u9078\u6319 |trans-title=37th single selection elections | work = AKB48 Official Site | language=Japanese}}</ref> In that year's rock-paper-scissors tournament, Miyawaki lost in the 3rd round of the preliminary competition. However, management decided she would share the center position with winner [[Mayu Watanabe]] for AKB48's 38th single, \"[[Kiboteki Refrain]]\", and became the first local HKT48 member to center on an A-side single.<ref name=\"kiboteki MV\">{{cite AV media | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j48VdEIKKHU | title=\u3010MV\u3011\u5e0c\u671b\u7684\u30ea\u30d5\u30ec\u30a4\u30f3 Short ver. / AKB48[\u516c\u5f0f] | date = October 29, 2014 | author=AKB48 | authorlink=AKB48 }}</ref><ref name=\"senbatsu\">{{cite web|title=AKB48\u3001\u65b0\u66f2\u9078\u629c\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc32\u4eba\u767a\u8868\u3000W\u30bb\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc\u306f\uff1f|url=http://mdpr.jp/news/detail/1419847|website=Modelpress|accessdate=January 27, 2015|language=Japanese|date=September 17, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://akbzine.com/2015/07/17/sakuras-touching-response-fan-discussion/|title=Miyawaki Sakura's touching response to a fan discussion|date=July 17, 2015}}</ref><!-- interview with Miyawaki -->\n\nIn 2015, Miyawaki was given a lead role in AKB48's drama ''[[Majisuka Gakuen|Majisuka Gakuen 4]]'' along with [[Haruka Shimazaki]]. The season premiered on January 19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tokyogirlsupdate.com/akb48-majisuka-gakuen-4-drama-20150133845.html|title=Details on AKB48 Groups' Drama Series \"Majisuka Gakuen 4\" Revealed!|website=Japanese kawaii idol music culture news &#124; Tokyo Girls Update}}</ref> She placed 7th overall in the general election the same year with 81,422 votes.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://aramajapan.com/news/results-of-the-akb48-41st-single-elections-are-out/19283/|title= Results of the AKB48 41st single elections are out!|date= June 6, 2015|accessdate= June 6, 2015|work= aramajapan.com}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2015, she released her first photobook, titled ''Sakura'' which reached number 1 on the weekly Oricon photobook chart and number 3 on the general book chart.<ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2056039/full/ |title=\u3010\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u3011\u5bae\u8107\u54b2\u826f\u3001\u521d\u5199\u771f\u96c6\u304c\u90e8\u95801\u4f4d \u7dcf\u5408\u30823\u4f4d\u30e9\u30f3\u30af\u30a4\u30f3 |work= [[ORICON NEWS]] |date= 2015-07-16 |accessdate= 2017-05-04 |language= ja}}</ref>\n\nOn AKB's 43rd single, \"[[Kimi wa Melody]]\", released March 9, 2016, she got her first solo center on an AKB48 single.\n\nIn 2018, Miyawaki participated and placed second in reality girl group survival show ''[[Produce 48]]'' and became a member of Korean-Japanese idol group [[Iz*One]] that debuted in October that same year. She and the other two Japanese members of the group will take a hiatus from their respective Japanese groups until their contracts with Iz*One expire in April 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/popasia/blog/2018/09/25/japanese-izone-members-take-hiatus-akb48|title=Japanese IZ*ONE members to take hiatus from AKB48|website=SBS PopAsia|language=en|access-date=2018-09-29}}</ref> Miyawaki has also started her own video gaming channel on [[YouTube]].\n\nFollowing the [[Mnet vote manipulation investigation]], Miyawaki's Japanese radio show was suspended on November 28, 2019.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2149639/full/ | title=IZ*ONE\u3001\u65e5\u672c\u3067\u306e\u5404\u7a2e\u30a4\u30d9\u30f3\u30c8\u304c\u5ef6\u671f\u306b | language=ja | work=[[Oricon]] | date=2019-11-28 | accessdate=2019-11-28}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{See also|AKB48|HKT48}}\n\n==Stage units==\n; Team H 1st Stage \"Te wo Tsunaginara\" (Hand in Hand)\n* \"Wimbledon e Tsureteitte\" (Take Me to Wimbledon)\n; Team H Waiting Stage \"Hakata Legend\"\n* \"Glass no I Love You\" (Glass-like I Love You)\n* \"Seifuku no Bambi\" (Bambi in a School Uniform)\n; HKT48's Himawarigumi 1st Stage \"Pajama Drive\"\n* \"Pajama Drive\"\n; Team A 5th Stage \"Renai Kinshi J\u014drei\" (Revival) (Rules Against Love)\n* \"Heart Gata Virus\" (Heart-shaped Virus)\n; Team KIV 1st Stage \"Theater no Megami\" (Goddess of the Theater)\n* \"Candy\"\n; HKT48's Himawarigumi 2nd Stage \"Tadaima Renaich\u016b\" (I'm in Love Right Now)\n* \"Junai no Crescendo\" (Pure Love's Crescendo)\n; Team A 7th Stage \"M.T. ni Sasagu\" (Dedicated to M.T.)\n* \"Yume de Kiss Me!\" (Kiss Me in My Dream!)\n; Team KIV 2nd Stage \"Saish\u016b Bell ga Naru\" (The Last Bell Rings)\n* \"Gomen ne Jewel\" (I'm Sorry, My Jewel)\n; HKT48's Himawarigumi 3rd Stage \"Y\u016bwaku no Garter\" (My Seducing Garter)\n* \"Saturday Night Party\"\n* \"Never!\"\n* \"I'm sure.\"\n; Team KIV 3rd Stage \"Seifuku no Me\" (Sprout of School Uniform)\n* \"Kareha no Station\" (Station of Dry Leaves)\n\n==Filmography==\n===TV dramas===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Network\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Source\n! class=\"unsortable | Notes\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''Ano Hito no Ano Hi''\n| Nazuna Imagawa\n| [[NHK General TV]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.allcinema.net/prog/show_p.php?num_p=902862|title= \u5bae\u8107\u54b2\u826f|accessdate= June 6, 2015|work= allcinema|publisher= Stingray|language= Japanese}}</ref>\n|[[Television film]]\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Himitsu''\n|Mari\n| [[Fukuoka Broadcasting Corporation|FBS]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.ent-mabui.jp/program/4270|title= HKT48\u30c9\u30e9\u30de\u30b9\u30da\u30b7\u30e3\u30eb\u300c\u79d8\u5bc6\u300d|accessdate= July 29, 2018|publisher= Entertainment Mabui|language= Japanese}}</ref>\n| Television film\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"| 2015\n| ''[[Majisuka Gakuen#4th Season Cast|Majisuka Gakuen 4]]''\n| Sakura Miyawaki\n| [[Nippon TV|NTV]]\n|\n| Lead role\n|-\n| ''[[Majisuka Gakuen#5th Season Cast|Majisuka Gakuen 5]]''\n| Sakura Miyawaki\n| NTV, [[Hulu]]\n|\n|Lead role\n|-\n|''AKB Horror Night: Adrenaline's Night''\n|Juri\n|[[TV Asahi]]\n|\n| Episode 5: \"Doppelg\u00e4nger\"\n|-\n|''[[Majisuka Gakuen#Spin-Off Season: 0: Kisarazu Rant\u014dhen|Majisuka Gakuen 0]]''\n|Sakura Miyawaki\n|NTV, Hulu\n|\n|Television film; lead role\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 2016\n|''[[Crow's Blood]]''\n|Maki Togawa\n|Hulu\n|<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-05-19/hulu-horror-series-crow-blood-teaser-show-akb48-idols/.102268|title  =Hulu Horror Series Crow's Blood's Teaser Show AKB48 Idols (Updated)|date= May 19, 2016|accessdate= May 20, 2016|work= [[Anime News Network]]}}</ref>\n| Lead role\n|-\n| ''AKB Love Night: Love Factory''\n| Nao\n| TV Asahi\n|\n| Episode 29: \"Guruguru Curtain\"\n|-\n|''Doctor-Y: Surgeon Hideki Kaji''\n|Haruka Mifune\n|[[au (mobile phone company)|au VideoPass]], TV Asahi [http://www.tv-asahi.co.jp/douga/ douga]\n|<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2077291/full/|title  =\u52dd\u6751\u653f\u4fe1\u3001\u300e\u30c9\u30af\u30bf\u30fcX\u300f\u30b9\u30d4\u30f3\u30aa\u30d5\u4e3b\u5f79\u306b\u9a5a\u304d\u300c\u30de\u30b8\u304b\u3088!\u300d|date= September 2, 2016|accessdate= July 29, 2018|publisher= [[Oricon]]|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n| Webdrama\n|-\n|[[Y\u016bsha Yoshihiko#Season 3|''The Hero Yoshihiko and the Seven Chosen Ones'']]\n|School idol group member\n| [[TV Tokyo]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.tv-tokyo.co.jp/yoshihiko/cast/chara199.html|title  =\u5973\u5b50\u9ad8\u751f4(HKT48\uff1a\u5bae\u8107\u54b2\u826f)\uff1a\u52c7\u8005\u30e8\u30b7\u30d2\u30b3\u5b8c\u5168\u56f3\u9451\uff1a\u30c6\u30ec\u30d3\u6771\u4eac|accessdate= July 29, 2018|publisher= [[TV Tokyo]]|language= Japanese}}</ref>\n|Episode 9\n|-\n|2016\u20132017\n|''[[Cabasuka Gakuen]]''\n|Sakura Miyawaki\n|NTV\n|\n| Lead role\n|-\n|2017\n|''Tofu Pro-Wrestling''\n| Sakura Miyawaki/Cherry Miyawaki\n| TV Asahi\n|\n|Lead role\n|-\n|2018\n|''Shanghai Love Map''\n| Herself\n|[[iQiyi]]\n|\n| Cameo \n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://weibo.com/6331724356/Fu8FqA6W1|date=November 8, 2017|title=\u5973\u5b69\u4eec\uff0c\u522b\u518d\u6000\u62b1\u739b\u4e3d\u82cf\u5e7b\u60f3|publisher=\u604b\u7231\u5730\u56fe\u4e0a\u6d77\u7bc7|language=zh-cn|accessdate=March 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://english.shukanbunshun.com/2017/10/miyawaki-sakura-start-new-drama.html|title=Miyawaki Sakura drama Shanghai Love Map|date=2017-10-16|accessdate=2017-10-17|publisher=Shukan Bunshun|language=English}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n===Variety show===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Network\n! Notes\n! Ref.\n|-\n| 2018\n| rowspan=\"2\" | ''[[Everyone's Kitchen]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Cast\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[O'live]]\n| Pilot, Trial broadcast\n|<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.soompi.com/article/1285213wpp/izones-miyawaki-sakura-talks-difficulties-living-dorm-12-girls|title= IZ*ONE's Miyawaki Sakura Talks About Difficulties Of Living In A Dorm With 12 Girls|accessdate= January 9, 2019|work= [[Soompi]]|publisher= Soompi|language= en}}</ref>\n|-\n|2019\n|Regular show\n|\n|}\n\n==Bibliography==\n===Solo photobooks===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|- style=\"background:#CCCCCC;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\"| #\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Release date\n! colspan=\"2\"| Charts\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Publisher\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n!width=\"35\"| JP<br /><small>[[Oricon]]<br />PB</small><br /><ref>\u5bae\u8107\u54b2\u826f\u30d5\u30a1\u30fc\u30b9\u30c8\u5199\u771f\u96c6\u300c\u3055\u304f\u3089\u300d<br />{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/obp/w/2015-07-20/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150722114612/http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/obp/w/2015-07-20/|archivedate=2015-07-22|title=\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u9031\u9593 \u5199\u771f\u96c6\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2015\u5e7407\u670806\u65e5\uff5e2015\u5e7407\u670812\u65e5|work=[[ORICON STYLE]]|accessdate=2017-05-04}}</ref>\n!width=\"35\"| JP<br /><small>[[Oricon]]<br />Books</small><br /><ref>\u5bae\u8107\u54b2\u826f\u30d5\u30a1\u30fc\u30b9\u30c8\u5199\u771f\u96c6\u300c\u3055\u304f\u3089\u300d<br />{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/ob/w/2015-07-20/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150722152843/http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/ob/w/2015-07-20/|archivedate=2015-07-22|title=\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u9031\u9593 BOOK\u7dcf\u5408\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2015\u5e7407\u670806\u65e5\uff5e2015\u5e7407\u670812\u65e5|work=[[ORICON STYLE]]|accessdate=2017-05-04}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1\n| align=\"left\"|{{nihongo|''Sakura''<br />&nbsp;|\u5bae\u8107\u54b2\u826f\u30d5\u30a1\u30fc\u30b9\u30c8\u5199\u771f\u96c6\u300c\u3055\u304f\u3089\u300d}}\n| align=\"center\"| July 2015\n| align=\"center\"| 1\n| align=\"center\"| 3\n| align=\"left\"| [[Shueisha]]\n|}\n\n== Radio Hosting ==\n''{{ill|Tonight, Under the Sakura Tree|ja|\u4eca\u591c\u3001\u54b2\u826f\u306e\u6728\u306e\u4e0b\u3067}} (''\u4eca\u591c\u3001\u54b2\u826f\u306e\u6728\u306e\u4e0b\u3067'') April 6, 2017 [[Bay FM (Japan)|Bay FM]]''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Portal|Music}}\n* [http://www.hkt48.jp/profile/sakura_miyawaki.html HKT48 Official Profile] {{in lang|ja}}\n<!-- * [http://www.akb48.co.jp/about/members/detail.php?name=miyawaki_sakura_akb AKB48 Official Profile] {{in lang|ja}} -->\n\n{{Iz*One}}\n{{HKT48}}\n{{AKB48}}\n{{Produce 101}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Miyawaki, Sakura}}\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Japanese actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Japanese singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century women singers]]\n[[Category:AKB48 members]]\n[[Category:HKT48 members]]\n[[Category:Iz*One members]]\n[[Category:Japanese idols]]\n[[Category:Japanese expatriates in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Japanese female pop singers]]\n[[Category:Japanese K-pop singers]]\n[[Category:Japanese television actresses]]\n[[Category:Korean-language singers of Japan]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Kagoshima Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Produce 48 contestants]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Japanese singer}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Sakura Miyawaki\n| image              = Sakura Miyawaki at Music Bank on April 12, 2019.png<!--Please do not change without providing a reason -->\n| alt                = \n| caption            = Miyawaki at Music Bank in April 2019\n| native_name        = \u5bae\u8107 \u54b2\u826f\n| native_name_lang   = ja\n| birth_name         = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1998|3|19|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Kagoshima]], Japan\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| residence          = \n| alias              = Sakura\n| occupation         = Singer, actress\n| years_active       = 2008<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nuts-pro.com/cgi-bin/info_view.cgi|title=WHATS NEW -NUTS PRODUCTION-|date=January 13, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140113014205/http://www.nuts-pro.com/cgi-bin/info_view.cgi|archive-date=2014-01-13}}</ref>\u2013present\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist\n| embed           = yes <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| background      = solo_singer\n| genre           = {{flatlist|\n* [[J-pop]]\n* [[K-pop]]}}\n| instrument      = Vocals\n| label           = {{flatlist|\n* [[AKS (company)|AKS]]\n* Off The Record   \n}}\n| associated_acts = {{hlist|[[HKT48]]|[[AKB48]]|[[Iz*One]]|}}\n}}\n| module2            = {{Infobox YouTube personality|embed=yes\n| channel_url         = https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC9Z0cgZPBa2szfjcrJdfYvA\n| channel_display_name = Channel Sakura Miyawaki\n| years_active      = 2018-present\n| genre             = [[Video game|Gaming]]\n| subscribers       = 516,000\n| subscriber_date   = April 2, 2020\n| views             = 14,780,958\n| view_date         = April 2, 2020\n| silver_button     = yes\n| silver_year       = 2018\n}}\n| module3            = {{Infobox Chinese | child= yes\n| kanji             = \u5bae\u8107 \u54b2\u826f\n| romaji            = Miyawaki Sakura\n| hiragana          = \u307f\u3084\u308f\u304d \u3055\u304f\u3089\n| katakana          = \u30df\u30e4\u30ef\u30ad \u30b5\u30af\u30e9\n}}\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Sakura Miyawaki'''|\u5bae\u8107 \u54b2\u826f|Miyawaki Sakura|born 19 March 1998}} is a Japanese singer and actress. She became a member of Japanese-South Korean girl group [[Iz*One]] after finishing second in survival reality television show ''[[Produce 48]]'' and is a member of the Japanese [[Japanese idol|idol]] girl group [[HKT48]].\n\nIn the General Elections of [[AKB48]], she has placed 47th (2012), 26th (2013), 11th (2014), 7th (2015), 6th (2016), 4th (2017), and 3rd (2018).\n\nAs one of the group's leading members, Miyawaki became the center (leading singer and dancer) of AKB48's 43rd single \"[[Kimi wa Melody]]\" (Your Melody) which is also AKB48's 10th Anniversary Memorial single in January 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tokyogirlsupdate.com/sakura-akb48-43rd-kimi-wa-melody-20160176740.html|title=AKB48's 43rd Single \"Kimi wa Melody\" Revealed on Final Day of Request Hour 2016!|website=Japanese kawaii idol music culture news {{!}} Tokyo Girls Update|access-date=2016-04-16}}</ref> In 2017, together with [[Jurina Matsui]] from SKE48, the two next generation aces that are also known as \"JuriSaku\" were chosen to be the WCenter (double centers) for AKB48 group commemorative 48th single \"[[Negaigoto no Mochigusare]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jpopasia.com/feed/20951/akb48-announces-9th-senbatsu-general-election-48th-single|work=J-pop Asia|title=AKB48 Announces 9th Senbatsu General Election + 48th Single|date=March 20, 2017|accessdate=March 20, 2019|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Miyawaki joined the show ''[[Produce 48]]'' and was selected as the center of the show's theme song, \"[[Nekkoya (Pick Me)|Nekkoya]]\". She placed 2nd and debuted on October 29, 2018 as a member of [[Iz*One]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=241&aid=0002776907|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5]\ubbf8\uc57c\uc640\ud0a4 \uc0ac\ucfe0\ub77c, '\ud504\ub85c\ub4c0\uc2a4 48' \uc13c\ud130\ub410\ub2e4|last=|first=|date=|work=Naver|access-date=|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nMiyawaki joined [[HKT48]] as a first generation trainee in July 2011. She made her first official appearance as an HKT48 member on October 23 at a national handshake event for the song \"[[Flying Get]]\". She made her theater debut on November 26 with a revival of [[SKE48]] Team S stage \"Te wo Tsunaginagara\".<ref>{{cite news|title=HKT48\u3001\u5730\u5143\u535a\u591a\u3067\u300c\u624b\u3092\u3064\u306a\u304e\u306a\u304c\u3089\u300d\u516c\u6f14\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc\u30c8|author=|url=http://news.nicovideo.jp/watch/nw152778|work=Natalie Music|date=November 11, 2011|accessdate=March 20, 2019|language=ja}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/music/2002974/full/ |title=HKT48\u3001\u897f\u6b66\u30c9\u30fc\u30e0\u3067\u521d\u4ee321\u4eba\u304a\u62ab\u9732\u76ee\u3000AKB\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u6700\u5e74\u5c11\u306e\u5e73\u5747\u5e74\u9f6213.8\u6b73 |date=October 23, 2011|accessdate=March 20, 2019|work=Oricon, Inc. |language=Ja}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.tokyohive.com/2011/11/hkt48-makes-their-theater-debut/ |title=HKT48 makes their theater debut|date=November 27, 2011|accessdate=March 20, 2019|work=Tokyohive|language=en}}</ref>\n\nMiyawaki was officially promoted to full member status of HKT48 Team H on March 4, 2012, along with 15 other trainees.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://ameblo.jp/hkt48/entry-11181717875.html|title=HKT48 \u30c1\u30fc\u30e0\uff28\u304a\u62ab\u9732\u76ee\u516c\u6f14\u7d42\u4e86|date=March 4, 2012 |accessdate=March 20, 2019|work= HKT48 official blog|language=Ja}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tokyohive.com/article/2012/03/hkt48-introduces-the-members-of-team-h|title=HKT48 introduces the members of 'Team H'|date=November 27, 2011|accessdate=March 20, 2019|work=Tokyohive|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, Miyawaki became the first HKT48 member  to have ranked in the AKB48 general election. She received 6,635 votes, placing her at the 47th position.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://japan.techinsight.jp/2012/06/hktmiyawaki-senbatu-rkb20120610.html|title=\u3010\u30a8\u30f3\u30bf\u304c\u30d3\u30bf\u30df\u30f3\u266a\u3011\u300c\u982d\u304c\u771f\u3063\u767d\u306b\u306a\u3063\u305f\u300d\u3002AKB\u9078\u629c\u7dcf\u9078\u631947\u4f4d\u3002HKT48\u5bae\u8107\u54b2\u826f\u304c\u751f\u653e\u9001\u3067\u5fc3\u5883\u8a9e\u308b\u3002|date=June 11, 2012|website=Techinsight\uff08\u30c6\u30c3\u30af\u30a4\u30f3\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8\uff09&#124;\u6d77\u5916\u30bb\u30ec\u30d6\u3001\u56fd\u5185\u30a8\u30f3\u30bf\u30e1\u306e\u30aa\u30f3\u30ea\u30fc\u30ef\u30f3\u3092\u304a\u5c4a\u3051\u3059\u308b\u30cb\u30e5\u30fc\u30b9\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8}}</ref> Later that year, she landed her first A-side participation on AKB48's 28th single \"[[Uza (song)|Uza]]\". Although she did not make the A-side for the 29th and 30th singles, she appeared on the A-side for the 31st single, \"[[Sayonara Crawl]]\", released on May 22, 2013, and placed 26th overall in AKB48's 2013 general election with 25,760 votes.<ref name=\"election2013\">{{cite web|url=http://www.akb48.co.jp/sousenkyo/32ndsingle/result.php|title = AKB48 32nd\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb \u9078\u629c\u7dcf\u9078\u6319 |trans-title=32nd single selection elections | work = AKB48 Official Site | date = 2013-06-08 | language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nMiyawaki's first A-side participation with HKT48 was on its first single \"[[Suki! Suki! Skip!]]\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hkt48.jp/discography/single/006115.html|title=\u30c7\u30a3\u30b9\u30b3\u30b0\u30e9\u30d5\u30a3\u30fc - \u30b9\u30ad\uff01\u30b9\u30ad\uff01\u30b9\u30ad\u30c3\u30d7\uff01|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130814111225/http://www.hkt48.jp/discography/single/006115.html|archive-date=2013-08-14|df=}}</ref> (Like! Like! Skip!) and [[Melon Juice (HKT48 song)|Melon Juice]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hkt48.jp/discography/single/007474.html|title=\u30c7\u30a3\u30b9\u30b3\u30b0\u30e9\u30d5\u30a3\u30fc - \u30e1\u30ed\u30f3\u30b8\u30e5\u30fc\u30b9|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140220151822/http://www.hkt48.jp/discography/single/007474.html|archive-date=2014-02-20|df=}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 January 2014, it was announced during the first day of [[HKT48]]'s Kyushu 7 Prefecture Tour at Oita, that Miyawaki would be transferred to the newly formed Team KIV.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2032880/full/|title=HKT48\u3001\u65b0\u30c1\u30fc\u30e0\u300cKIV\u300d\u767a\u8db3\uff06\u521d\u518d\u7de8 \u6307\u539f\u5287\u5834\u652f\u914d\u4eba\u304c\"\u30af\u30e9\u30b9\u66ff\u3048\"\u767a\u8868|website=ORICON NEWS}}</ref> Later, at AKB48's Group Grand Reformation Festival, she was promoted to vice captain of Team KIV and given a concurrent position in AKB48 Team A.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://realsound.jp/2014/02/akb48ske48nmb4846.html|title=AKB48\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u300c\u5927\u7d44\u95a3\u796d\u308a\u300d\u901f\u5831 \u4e43\u6728\u574246\u751f\u99d2\u3001SKE48\u6728\u5d0e\u306a\u3069\u306e\u4ef0\u5929\u4eba\u4e8b\u3082\u7d9a\u3005|website=Real Sound\uff5c\u30ea\u30a2\u30eb\u30b5\u30a6\u30f3\u30c9}}</ref>\n\nMiyawaki participated in the 2014 AKB48 general election and placed 11th overall with 45,538 votes, landing her a position on the A-side for \"[[Kokoro no Placard]]\".<ref name=\"election2014\">{{cite web|url=http://www.akb48.co.jp/sousenkyo/37thsingle/result.php|title = AKB48 37th\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb \u9078\u629c\u7dcf\u9078\u6319 |trans-title=37th single selection elections | work = AKB48 Official Site | language=Japanese}}</ref> In that year's rock-paper-scissors tournament, Miyawaki lost in the 3rd round of the preliminary competition. However, management decided she would share the center position with winner [[Mayu Watanabe]] for AKB48's 38th single, \"[[Kiboteki Refrain]]\", and became the first local HKT48 member to center on an A-side single.<ref name=\"kiboteki MV\">{{cite AV media | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j48VdEIKKHU | title=\u3010MV\u3011\u5e0c\u671b\u7684\u30ea\u30d5\u30ec\u30a4\u30f3 Short ver. / AKB48[\u516c\u5f0f] | date = October 29, 2014 | author=AKB48 | authorlink=AKB48 }}</ref><ref name=\"senbatsu\">{{cite web|title=AKB48\u3001\u65b0\u66f2\u9078\u629c\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc32\u4eba\u767a\u8868\u3000W\u30bb\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc\u306f\uff1f|url=http://mdpr.jp/news/detail/1419847|website=Modelpress|accessdate=January 27, 2015|language=Japanese|date=September 17, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://akbzine.com/2015/07/17/sakuras-touching-response-fan-discussion/|title=Miyawaki Sakura's touching response to a fan discussion|date=July 17, 2015}}</ref><!-- interview with Miyawaki -->\n\nIn 2015, Miyawaki was given a lead role in AKB48's drama ''[[Majisuka Gakuen|Majisuka Gakuen 4]]'' along with [[Haruka Shimazaki]]. The season premiered on January 19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tokyogirlsupdate.com/akb48-majisuka-gakuen-4-drama-20150133845.html|title=Details on AKB48 Groups' Drama Series \"Majisuka Gakuen 4\" Revealed!|website=Japanese kawaii idol music culture news &#124; Tokyo Girls Update}}</ref> She placed 7th overall in the general election the same year with 81,422 votes.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://aramajapan.com/news/results-of-the-akb48-41st-single-elections-are-out/19283/|title= Results of the AKB48 41st single elections are out!|date= June 6, 2015|accessdate= June 6, 2015|work= aramajapan.com}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2015, she released her first photobook, titled ''Sakura'' which reached number 1 on the weekly Oricon photobook chart and number 3 on the general book chart.<ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2056039/full/ |title=\u3010\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u3011\u5bae\u8107\u54b2\u826f\u3001\u521d\u5199\u771f\u96c6\u304c\u90e8\u95801\u4f4d \u7dcf\u5408\u30823\u4f4d\u30e9\u30f3\u30af\u30a4\u30f3 |work= [[ORICON NEWS]] |date= 2015-07-16 |accessdate= 2017-05-04 |language= ja}}</ref>\n\nOn AKB's 43rd single, \"[[Kimi wa Melody]]\", released March 9, 2016, she got her first solo center on an AKB48 single.\n\nIn 2018, Miyawaki participated and placed second in reality girl group survival show ''[[Produce 48]]'' and became a member of Korean-Japanese idol group [[Iz*One]] that debuted in October that same year. She and the other two Japanese members of the group will take a hiatus from their respective Japanese groups until their contracts with Iz*One expire in April 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/popasia/blog/2018/09/25/japanese-izone-members-take-hiatus-akb48|title=Japanese IZ*ONE members to take hiatus from AKB48|website=SBS PopAsia|language=en|access-date=2018-09-29}}</ref> Miyawaki has also started her own video gaming channel on [[YouTube]].\n\nFollowing the [[Mnet vote manipulation investigation]], Miyawaki's Japanese radio show was suspended on November 28, 2019.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2149639/full/ | title=IZ*ONE\u3001\u65e5\u672c\u3067\u306e\u5404\u7a2e\u30a4\u30d9\u30f3\u30c8\u304c\u5ef6\u671f\u306b | language=ja | work=[[Oricon]] | date=2019-11-28 | accessdate=2019-11-28}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{See also|AKB48|HKT48}}\n\n==Stage units==\n; Team H 1st Stage \"Te wo Tsunaginara\" (Hand in Hand)\n* \"Wimbledon e Tsureteitte\" (Take Me to Wimbledon)\n; Team H Waiting Stage \"Hakata Legend\"\n* \"Glass no I Love You\" (Glass-like I Love You)\n* \"Seifuku no Bambi\" (Bambi in a School Uniform)\n; HKT48's Himawarigumi 1st Stage \"Pajama Drive\"\n* \"Pajama Drive\"\n; Team A 5th Stage \"Renai Kinshi J\u014drei\" (Revival) (Rules Against Love)\n* \"Heart Gata Virus\" (Heart-shaped Virus)\n; Team KIV 1st Stage \"Theater no Megami\" (Goddess of the Theater)\n* \"Candy\"\n; HKT48's Himawarigumi 2nd Stage \"Tadaima Renaich\u016b\" (I'm in Love Right Now)\n* \"Junai no Crescendo\" (Pure Love's Crescendo)\n; Team A 7th Stage \"M.T. ni Sasagu\" (Dedicated to M.T.)\n* \"Yume de Kiss Me!\" (Kiss Me in My Dream!)\n; Team KIV 2nd Stage \"Saish\u016b Bell ga Naru\" (The Last Bell Rings)\n* \"Gomen ne Jewel\" (I'm Sorry, My Jewel)\n; HKT48's Himawarigumi 3rd Stage \"Y\u016bwaku no Garter\" (My Seducing Garter)\n* \"Saturday Night Party\"\n* \"Never!\"\n* \"I'm sure.\"\n; Team KIV 3rd Stage \"Seifuku no Me\" (Sprout of School Uniform)\n* \"Kareha no Station\" (Station of Dry Leaves)\n\n==Filmography==\n===TV dramas===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Network\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Source\n! class=\"unsortable | Notes\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''Ano Hito no Ano Hi''\n| Nazuna Imagawa\n| [[NHK General TV]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.allcinema.net/prog/show_p.php?num_p=902862|title= \u5bae\u8107\u54b2\u826f|accessdate= June 6, 2015|work= allcinema|publisher= Stingray|language= Japanese}}</ref>\n|[[Television film]]\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Himitsu''\n|Mari\n| [[Fukuoka Broadcasting Corporation|FBS]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.ent-mabui.jp/program/4270|title= HKT48\u30c9\u30e9\u30de\u30b9\u30da\u30b7\u30e3\u30eb\u300c\u79d8\u5bc6\u300d|accessdate= July 29, 2018|publisher= Entertainment Mabui|language= Japanese}}</ref>\n| Television film\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"| 2015\n| ''[[Majisuka Gakuen#4th Season Cast|Majisuka Gakuen 4]]''\n| Sakura Miyawaki\n| [[Nippon TV|NTV]]\n|\n| Lead role\n|-\n| ''[[Majisuka Gakuen#5th Season Cast|Majisuka Gakuen 5]]''\n| Sakura Miyawaki\n| NTV, [[Hulu]]\n|\n|Lead role\n|-\n|''AKB Horror Night: Adrenaline's Night''\n|Juri\n|[[TV Asahi]]\n|\n| Episode 5: \"Doppelg\u00e4nger\"\n|-\n|''[[Majisuka Gakuen#Spin-Off Season: 0: Kisarazu Rant\u014dhen|Majisuka Gakuen 0]]''\n|Sakura Miyawaki\n|NTV, Hulu\n|\n|Television film; lead role\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 2016\n|''[[Crow's Blood]]''\n|Maki Togawa\n|Hulu\n|<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-05-19/hulu-horror-series-crow-blood-teaser-show-akb48-idols/.102268|title  =Hulu Horror Series Crow's Blood's Teaser Show AKB48 Idols (Updated)|date= May 19, 2016|accessdate= May 20, 2016|work= [[Anime News Network]]}}</ref>\n| Lead role\n|-\n| ''AKB Love Night: Love Factory''\n| Nao\