lign=\"center\"| 1\n| align=\"center\"| 3\n| align=\"left\"| [[Shueisha]]\n|}\n\n== Radio Hosting ==\n''{{ill|Tonight, Under the Sakura Tree|ja|\u4eca\u591c\u3001\u54b2\u826f\u306e\u6728\u306e\u4e0b\u3067}} (''\u4eca\u591c\u3001\u54b2\u826f\u306e\u6728\u306e\u4e0b\u3067'') April 6, 2017 [[Bay FM (Japan)|Bay FM]]''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Portal|Music}}\n* [http://www.hkt48.jp/profile/sakura_miyawaki.html HKT48 Official Profile] {{in lang|ja}}\n<!-- * [http://www.akb48.co.jp/about/members/detail.php?name=miyawaki_sakura_akb AKB48 Official Profile] {{in lang|ja}} -->\n\n{{Iz*One}}\n{{HKT48}}\n{{AKB48}}\n{{Produce 101}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Miyawaki, Sakura}}\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Japanese actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Japanese singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century women singers]]\n[[Category:AKB48 members]]\n[[Category:HKT48 members]]\n[[Category:Iz*One members]]\n[[Category:Japanese idols]]\n[[Category:Japanese expatriates in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Japanese female pop singers]]\n[[Category:Japanese K-pop singers]]\n[[Category:Japanese television actresses]]\n[[Category:Korean-language singers of Japan]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Kagoshima Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Produce 48 contestants]]\n", "name_user": "122.53.234.5", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(fixed typo)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sakura_Miyawaki"}
{"title_page": "B\u1ea3o \u00c2n", "text_new": "{{BLP sources|date=June 2017}}{{Expand language|langcode=vi|date=April 2019}}{{Infobox royalty\n| name        = Nguy\u1ec5n Ph\u00fac B\u1ea3o \u00c2n\n| image       = [[File:Bao An.jpg|250px]]\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1952|11|3|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[\u0110\u00e0 L\u1ea1t]], [[French Indochina]]\n| death_date  = \n| death_place = \n| regnal      =\n| title       = Prince\n| succession  = Pretender to the Vietnamese throne\n| reign       = 15 March 2017 \u2013 present\n| reign-type  = Pretendence\n| year        = 1955\n| house       = [[Nguy\u1ec5n dynasty]]\n| father      = [[B\u1ea3o \u0110\u1ea1i]]\n| mother      = {{ill|L\u00ea Th\u1ecb Phi \u00c1nh|vi}}\n| spouse      = \n| issue       = Th\u1ee5y S\u0129 <small>(Daughter)</small><br>Qu\u00fd Khang <small>(Son)</small>\n| predecessor = [[B\u1ea3o Th\u1eafng]]\n| successor   = '''Qu\u00fd Khang'''\n| footnotes   =\n}}\n\nPrince '''Nguy\u1ec5n Ph\u00fac B\u1ea3o \u00c2n''' (born November 3, 1952, in [[\u0110\u00e0 L\u1ea1t]], [[Vietnam]]) is the youngest son of Emperor [[B\u1ea3o \u0110\u1ea1i]] and concubine {{ill|L\u00ea Th\u1ecb Phi \u00c1nh|vi}}.<ref>[http://www.nguoi-viet.com/little-saigon/Gap-go-Me-Bao-An-con-trai-ut-cua-Cuu-Hoang-Bao-Dai-0604/ G\u1eb7p g\u1ee1 \u201cM\u1ec7\u201d B\u1ea3o \u00c2n, con trai \u00fat c\u1ee7a C\u1ef1u Ho\u00e0ng B\u1ea3o \u00d0\u1ea1i] March 18, 2013 (Vietnamese Language Only)</ref>  He became the head of the [[Nguy\u1ec5n dynasty]] following the death of his half brother, [[B\u1ea3o Th\u1eafng]], on 15 March 2017, since B\u1ea3o Th\u1eafng had no children.<ref>[http://www.dansnoscoeurs.fr/prince-bao-thang/2041393/avis]</ref>\n\n==Title==\n*[[His Imperial Highness]] Prince B\u1ea3o \u00c2n.{{citation needed|date=June 2017}}\n\n==Ancestry==\n{{ahnentafel\n|collapsed=yes |align=center\n|boxstyle_1=background-color: #fcc;\n|boxstyle_2=background-color: #fb9;\n|boxstyle_3=background-color: #ffc;\n|boxstyle_4=backgr